President Barack Obama will award Ryan M. Pitts, a former Army Staff Sergeant, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan on July 13, 2008. Pitts will be the ninth living recipient to be awarded the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He currently lives in Nashua, New Hampshire and works in business development for the computer software industry. Pitts enlisted in the Army in 2003 and served in various roles before becoming a Forward Observer. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate exceptional bravery or self-sacrifice in the face of great personal risk.